SIMPLE: marbling
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Marbling
<hw>Mar"bling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The art
or practice of variegating in color, in imitation of marble.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An intermixture of fat and lean in meat, giving it a
marbled appearance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Distinct
markings resembling the variegations of marble, as on birds and
insects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Marbly</ent>⟦br⟧
